---
title: Spiced Smoked Salmon Pilaf with Spinach and Carrot
description: Quick, easy to prep and packed with fresh ingredients, our fragrant salmon pilaf is the perfect one-pot dish. The trick to a well-seasoned pilaf is to sauté the aromatics before adding the rice to the pan. Once the base is ready, add the rice and cook, stirring, until the grains are well-coated. Toasting the rice grains until they're coated in oil and start to look translucent helps them separate so they won't clump and gives the dish a real depth of flavour.
